get public methods from the public class. If the nested class is public static within a public test class, then perhaps the method should also be public. For the return type, I see it could be a String. We need to ensure the method signature is correct for public static String main(String[] arguments). I’ll also need to implement a fake evaluator, potentially within ClassBodyDemoTest, while keeping the factory in CompilerFactoryFactoryTest in mind for references.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reflecting on constructors**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the agent will gather reflections for the constructor. There’s an existing test that covers this, but I'm considering if ClassLoader.loadClass is being used correctly by name with a constant string from resource data. It seems like the native implementation may need a specific reflection configuration for the TestCompilerFactory constructor. I should note that there's existing metadata generated by the agent to consider as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Compiler Usage**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether the cached TestCompilerFactory utilizes any resources. It seems that `CompilerFactoryFactoryTest.discoversCompilerFactories...` calls the method getAllCompilerFactories on its ResourceBackedClassLoader, which implies that everything is functioning correctly. It's interesting to consider how these different components interact and how they're built. I just want to ensure that the setup is working as expected without creating unnecessary overhead.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RAB5VPhUSLENmDkVF5PcBatT|fc_0bbafbe82c6a6a790169f9401ef39881a2897aecd3815e7e25", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/src/test/java/org_codehaus_janino/commons_compiler/CompilerFactoryFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.codehaus.commons.compiler.ICompiler;\nimport org.codehaus.commons.compiler.ICompilerFactory;\n", "newText": "import